                        <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="27.0" layoutY="40.0" prefHeight="160.0" prefWidth="540.0" text="Status Editor&#10; - The status editor is used to state a reason behind an employee leave of absence. To enter a status click on Tools select Status in the drop down list and status editor will appear. To enter a status, enter a name in the title textbox and enter a name shortcut in the code textbox. For example: Title could be Leave and Code could be L. You can select the allow increment checkbox if they deem the leave to be unauthorized and you can uncheck the box if the leave is deemed to be authorized. More information about the increments can be found in Roster Priority, Duty Conflicts, and Rest Periods. Once all the information from the status has been entered, select the add button and it will appear in the editor list. To delete a status simply right click on the code and select delete option. If you choose to change the increment of the status, you can select or unselect the checkbox under ‘Inc’. If you would like to change the viewing order of the list select the title header and click on the arrow. &#10;&#10;Blockout Editor&#10; - The blockout editor is used to specify a leave time for an employee. To access the blockout editor, go to Tools and select the Blockout Editor in the drop down list and blockout editor will appear. Select a status and the name, to select the time frame of the leave, select the calendar icon and click a date or you can manually add the dates. Once the information is added, you can select the add button. If you would like to change the viewing order of the list select the title header and click on the arrow. To edit a blockout date, double click the row and it will appear again on the bottom of the editor, where you can edit the information. To save the new edits, select update button and to cancel select the cancel button. To delete a blockout date simply right click on the line and select delete option." wr